be root
$ sudo -s

Update sources and packages
$ apt-get update
$ apt-get upgrade

Install needed packages
$ apt-get install sudo
$ apt-get install vim
$ apt-get install -y mailutils
$ apt-get install -y ssmtp

Check running services
$ service --status-all

Add a non-root user
$ sudo adduser ehouzard

Add user to sudoers
$ sudo usermod -a -G sudo ehouzard

Switch to new user
$ su - ehouzard

Check
$ whoami

Edit sudoers file to avoid entering password each time sudo is used by adding following line
$ visudo
'
  ehouzard ALL=(ALL:ALL) NOPASSWD:ALL
'








Install web packages
$ apt-get install apache2
$ apt-get install mysql-server
$ apt-get install mysql-client
$ apt-get install phpmyadmin
$ apt-get install apt-transport-https ca-certificates curl software-properties-common
